reviewText: I have to admit that I bought this movie for myself. I am 71 & love dog movies. I am so disappointed in this movie. All I saw ,myself was almost an exact storyline as Beethoven's 4th, which to me was more realistic & I thought the antics were more "stupid" than "funny", & I am going to give it to my granddaughter & hope she likes it.

My family likes & owns "The Dog Who Saved Easter" & this movie is even better than that one.  It's somewhat similar to The Karate Kid & even has the evil Sensei (Martin Kove) from Karate Kid (1984) in this movie.  This is a really funny & cute movie.  I recommend it.

This is such a cute movie for kids.  My boys also have The Dog that Saves Easter and watch it even though Easter is over.  They were super excited when this DVD arrived and said it was just as good as the Easter one.

**I was sent this product in exchange for a honest review. The opinions above are my own.**

Loved it.  A great family show.  Love when they have to take the dog to obedience school.  Also love where they catch the burglars in the end.  Thought it was especially funny when the dog causes them to drop all the presents in the pool.
We recently lost our lab so we were excited to watch a lab movie.  The lab was cute but the movie was NOT.  Didn't finish watching it.
My 6 year old could not get enough of this movie.  He watched it multiple times.
Excellent movie, very funny and cute, good for children and adults.

Really enjoyed this one! I was worried it would suck since after a series does so many sequels, they lose their touch, but it surprised me. This is every enjoyable, fun and very cute. And it's nothing like Beethoven's 4th, I don't understand why a reviewer said this. Great for kids or animal lovers of all ages
Grandson loved it !
I loved this movie!  Great for the family and fun!  Another great addition to The Dog Who Saved series.
Too predictable, kids bored.
Very sweet and great film
This film had a slow and boring story line.  Our grandsons could have come up with a more interesting script!
It was cute and funny to watch if you like animal's this would be a good one to watch.

Fun comedy for the whole family, but aimed mostly for the younger age group (probably best for ages 7-11.)  If you have seen the old "Karate Kid" movies from the 80's, you'll notice a VERY familiar theme here - in this case, the dog taking the place of the Karate Kid - needing to learn certain tasks that will help him at the showdown.  A few characters from the original Karate Kid also make appearances in this flick!
the movie is ok but it isn't as good as the others.  maybe the next one will be funnier.  my family loves all of the other zeus movies we would love to see more.
Cute movie! I love the dog in this series of movies!

this is  a awesome movie. this is a great addition to the series. zeus is back and now he is in obedience school, for ruining Blenda's baby shower party that she did for a friend. the whole cast is back, except the kids in this fun in the sun movie for the whole family. can zeus graduate school and learn to behave or will he fail. and ted and Stewey are up to their no good tricks again. this is a great movie for the whole family. the story is good and the acting is good. if you have not seen this movie then i recommend you do
these movies are so cute
Such a cute kids/ family movie. It's sort of like a Karate Kid with dogs in place of the kids. In fact it has some of the original Karate Kid cast in it.
Was a funny movie I enjoyed it
I love this whole series. Wish they would come out with another new movie.
good
fine
